{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":903,"text":"Thirteen years ago,"},{"time":3069,"text":"we set ourselves a goal to end poverty."},{"time":9450,"text":"After some success,"},{"time":12069,"text":"we've hit a big hurdle."},{"time":15123,"text":"The aftermath of the financial crisis"},{"time":17644,"text":"has begun to hit aid payments,"},{"time":20369,"text":"which have fallen for two consecutive years."},{"time":25133,"text":"My question is whether the lessons learned"},{"time":29112,"text":"from saving the financial system"},{"time":33032,"text":"can be used to help us overcome that hurdle"},{"time":36514,"text":"and help millions."},{"time":39719,"text":"Can we simply print money for aid?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":46629,"text":"\"Surely not.\""},{"time":48136,"text":"It's a common reaction."},{"time":50145,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":51167,"text":"It's a quick talk."},{"time":53677,"text":"Others channel John McEnroe."},{"time":58454,"text":"\"You cannot be serious!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":60426,"text":"Now, I can't do the accent, but I am serious,"},{"time":65357,"text":"thanks to these two children,"},{"time":69357,"text":"who, as you'll learn, are very much at the heart"},{"time":73037,"text":"of my talk."},{"time":75529,"text":"On the left, we have Pia."},{"time":78495,"text":"She lives in England."},{"time":80085,"text":"She has two loving parents,"},{"time":83229,"text":"one of whom is standing right here."},{"time":88129,"text":"Dorothy, on the right,"},{"time":90521,"text":"lives in rural Kenya."},{"time":93420,"text":"She's one of 13,000 orphans"},{"time":96059,"text":"and vulnerable children"},{"time":97564,"text":"who are assisted by a charity that I support."},{"time":102912,"text":"I do that because I believe"},{"time":105692,"text":"that Dorothy, like Pia,"},{"time":108013,"text":"deserves the best life chances"},{"time":111351,"text":"that we can afford to give her."},{"time":113915,"text":"You'll all agree with me, I'm sure."},{"time":116954,"text":"The U.N. agrees too."},{"time":119564,"text":"Their overriding aim"},{"time":121616,"text":"for international aid"},{"time":123692,"text":"is to strive for a life of dignity for all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129834,"text":"But -- and here's that hurdle --"},{"time":134354,"text":"can we afford our aid aspirations?"},{"time":138904,"text":"History suggests not."},{"time":142197,"text":"In 1970, governments set themselves a target"},{"time":147519,"text":"to increase overseas aid payments"},{"time":150014,"text":"to 0.7 percent"},{"time":152283,"text":"of their national income."},{"time":153922,"text":"As you can see, a big gap opens up"},{"time":158199,"text":"between actual aid and that target."},{"time":162793,"text":"But then come the Millennium Development Goals,"},{"time":167056,"text":"eight ambitious targets"},{"time":169465,"text":"to be met by 2015."},{"time":173373,"text":"If I tell you that just one of those targets"},{"time":176368,"text":"is to eradicate extreme hunger and poverty,"},{"time":180551,"text":"you get a sense of the ambition."},{"time":183369,"text":"There's also been some success."},{"time":186974,"text":"The number of people living"},{"time":188283,"text":"on less than $1.25 a day has halved."},{"time":194259,"text":"But a lot remains to be done in two years."},{"time":197986,"text":"One in eight remain hungry."},{"time":201677,"text":"In the context of this auditorium,"},{"time":204288,"text":"the front two rows aren't going to get any food."},{"time":208736,"text":"We can't settle for that,"},{"time":210894,"text":"which is why the concern about the eighth goal,"},{"time":215398,"text":"which relates to funding,"},{"time":217218,"text":"which I said at the beginning is falling,"},{"time":220132,"text":"is so troubling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224592,"text":"So what can be done?"},{"time":226646,"text":"Well, I work in financial markets,"},{"time":229638,"text":"not development."},{"time":232089,"text":"I study the behavior of investors,"},{"time":235126,"text":"how they react to policy and the economy."},{"time":240712,"text":"It gives me a different angle on the aid issue."},{"time":245345,"text":"But it took an innocent question"},{"time":247866,"text":"from my then-four-year-old daughter"},{"time":250501,"text":"to make me appreciate that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254560,"text":"Pia and I were on the way to a local cafe"},{"time":257755,"text":"and we passed a man collecting for charity."},{"time":262171,"text":"I didn't have any change to give him,"},{"time":263722,"text":"and she was disappointed."},{"time":266223,"text":"Once in the cafe, Pia takes out her coloring book"},{"time":270001,"text":"and starts scribbling."},{"time":271743,"text":"After a little while, I ask her what she's doing,"},{"time":275767,"text":"and she shows me a drawing"},{"time":278303,"text":"of a Â£5 note"},{"time":280515,"text":"to give to the man outside."},{"time":282558,"text":"It's so sweet,"},{"time":283811,"text":"and more generous than Dad would have been."},{"time":286911,"text":"But of course I explained to her,"},{"time":288837,"text":"\"You can't do that; it's not allowed.\""},{"time":291340,"text":"To which I get the classic four-year-old response:"},{"time":296034,"text":"\"Why not?\""},{"time":298582,"text":"Now I'm excited, because I actually think"},{"time":300996,"text":"I can answer this time."},{"time":302837,"text":"So I launch into an explanation of how"},{"time":305752,"text":"an unlimited supply of money"},{"time":309067,"text":"chasing a limited number of goods"},{"time":312246,"text":"sends prices to the moon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319036,"text":"Something about that exchange stuck with me,"},{"time":323355,"text":"not because of the look of relief"},{"time":325458,"text":"on Pia's face when I finally finished,"},{"time":327721,"text":"but because it related"},{"time":332511,"text":"to the sanctity of the money supply,"},{"time":337412,"text":"a sanctity that had been challenged and questioned"},{"time":341714,"text":"by the reaction of central banks"},{"time":344633,"text":"to the financial crisis."},{"time":347109,"text":"To reassure investors,"},{"time":349676,"text":"central banks began buying assets"},{"time":354573,"text":"to try and encourage investors to do the same."},{"time":359609,"text":"They funded these purchases"},{"time":363207,"text":"with money they created themselves."},{"time":366756,"text":"The money wasn't actually physically printed."},{"time":370042,"text":"It's still sort of locked away\nin the banking system today."},{"time":373656,"text":"But the amount created was unprecedented."},{"time":378857,"text":"Together, the central banks of the U.S.,"},{"time":382362,"text":"U.K and Japan"},{"time":384232,"text":"increased the stock of money in their economies"},{"time":387622,"text":"by 3.7 trillion dollars."},{"time":391650,"text":"That's three times, in fact\nthat's more than three times,"},{"time":395105,"text":"the total physical stock of dollar notes in circulation."},{"time":399917,"text":"Three times!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":404165,"text":"Before the crisis,"},{"time":406075,"text":"this would have been utterly unthinkable,"},{"time":411023,"text":"yet it was accepted remarkably quickly."},{"time":418487,"text":"The price of gold,"},{"time":420514,"text":"an asset thought to protect against inflation,"},{"time":423262,"text":"did jump,"},{"time":426088,"text":"but investors bought other assets"},{"time":428886,"text":"that offered little protection from inflation."},{"time":431517,"text":"They bought fixed income securities, bonds."},{"time":435061,"text":"They bought equities too."},{"time":437828,"text":"For all the scare stories,"},{"time":440487,"text":"the actual actions of investors"},{"time":443516,"text":"spoke of rapid acceptance and confidence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450041,"text":"That confidence was based on two pillars."},{"time":455716,"text":"The first was that, after years"},{"time":458181,"text":"of keeping inflation under control,"},{"time":461437,"text":"central banks were trusted"},{"time":464244,"text":"to take the money-printing away"},{"time":467531,"text":"if inflation became a threat."},{"time":471152,"text":"Secondly, inflation simply never became a threat."},{"time":477381,"text":"As you can see, in the United States,"},{"time":479249,"text":"inflation for most of this period"},{"time":481290,"text":"remained below average."},{"time":484747,"text":"It was the same elsewhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488019,"text":"So how does all this relate to aid?"},{"time":491436,"text":"Well, this is where Dorothy"},{"time":495311,"text":"and the Mango Tree charity"},{"time":497777,"text":"that supports her comes in."},{"time":500335,"text":"I was at one of their fundraising events"},{"time":502432,"text":"earlier this year,"},{"time":503652,"text":"and I was inspired to give a one-off donation"},{"time":507401,"text":"when I remembered that my firm"},{"time":510239,"text":"offers to match the charitable contributions"},{"time":513498,"text":"its employees make."},{"time":516241,"text":"So think of this:"},{"time":518967,"text":"Instead of just being able to help Dorothy"},{"time":521254,"text":"and four of her classmates"},{"time":523960,"text":"to go through secondary school for a few years,"},{"time":526240,"text":"I was able to double my contribution."},{"time":530544,"text":"Brilliant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532957,"text":"So following that conversation with my daughter,"},{"time":538920,"text":"and seeing the absence of inflation"},{"time":541557,"text":"in the face of money-printing,"},{"time":543504,"text":"and knowing that international aid payments"},{"time":546591,"text":"were falling at just the wrong time,"},{"time":549903,"text":"this made me wonder:"},{"time":553864,"text":"Could we match"},{"time":555959,"text":"but just on a much grander scale?"},{"time":562009,"text":"Let's call this scheme \"Print Aid.\""},{"time":566462,"text":"And here's how it might work."},{"time":569120,"text":"Provided it saw little inflation risk from doing so,"},{"time":574277,"text":"the central bank would be mandated"},{"time":576587,"text":"to match the government's overseas aid payments"},{"time":579980,"text":"up to a certain limit."},{"time":582447,"text":"Governments have been aiming to get aid"},{"time":584520,"text":"to 0.7 percent for years,"},{"time":586238,"text":"so let's set the limit at half of that,"},{"time":589123,"text":"0.35 percent of their income."},{"time":593232,"text":"So it would work like this: If in a given year"},{"time":595304,"text":"the government gave 0.2 percent of its income"},{"time":597990,"text":"to overseas aid,"},{"time":599122,"text":"the central bank would simply top it up"},{"time":600605,"text":"with a further 0.2 percent."},{"time":603781,"text":"So far so good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607382,"text":"How risky is this?"},{"time":610062,"text":"Well, this involves the creation of money"},{"time":614304,"text":"to buy goods, not assets."},{"time":617112,"text":"It sounds more inflationary already, doesn't it."},{"time":620665,"text":"But there are two important mitigating factors here."},{"time":625093,"text":"The first is that by definition,"},{"time":628636,"text":"this money printed would be spent overseas."},{"time":633786,"text":"So it's not obvious how it leads to inflation"},{"time":637327,"text":"in the country doing the actual printing"},{"time":641736,"text":"unless it leads to a currency\ndepreciation of that country."},{"time":646670,"text":"That is unlikely for the second reason:"},{"time":649963,"text":"the scale of the money that would be printed"},{"time":652844,"text":"under this scheme."},{"time":655664,"text":"So let's think of an example"},{"time":658804,"text":"where Print Aid was in place"},{"time":662347,"text":"in the U.S., U.K. and Japan."},{"time":666689,"text":"To match the aid payments made"},{"time":668992,"text":"by those governments over the last four years,"},{"time":671728,"text":"Print Aid would have generated"},{"time":673955,"text":"200 billion dollars' worth of extra aid."},{"time":678290,"text":"What would that look like"},{"time":680477,"text":"in the context of the increase in the money stock"},{"time":684079,"text":"that had already happened in those countries"},{"time":686355,"text":"to save the financial system?"},{"time":688436,"text":"Are you read for this?"},{"time":691593,"text":"You might struggle to see that at the back,"},{"time":693677,"text":"because the gap is quite small."},{"time":697247,"text":"So what we're saying here"},{"time":699695,"text":"is that we took a $3.7 trillion gamble"},{"time":703163,"text":"to save our financial systems,"},{"time":705539,"text":"and you know what, it paid off."},{"time":707594,"text":"There was no inflation."},{"time":710167,"text":"Are we really saying that it's not worth the risk"},{"time":713473,"text":"to print an extra 200 billion for aid?"},{"time":718125,"text":"Would the risks really be that different?"},{"time":720034,"text":"To me, it's not that clear."},{"time":722577,"text":"What is clear is the impact on aid."},{"time":725935,"text":"Even though this is the printing"},{"time":728051,"text":"of just three central banks,"},{"time":729887,"text":"the global aid that's given"},{"time":733508,"text":"over this period is up by almost 40 percent."},{"time":738429,"text":"Aid as a proportion of national income"},{"time":740860,"text":"all of a sudden is at a 40-year high."},{"time":744310,"text":"Now, we don't get to 0.7 percent."},{"time":747297,"text":"Governments are still incentivized to give."},{"time":750042,"text":"But you know what, that's the \npoint of a matching scheme."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754535,"text":"So I think what we've learned"},{"time":758350,"text":"is that the risks from this money creation scheme"},{"time":762944,"text":"are quite modest,"},{"time":765725,"text":"but the benefits"},{"time":768525,"text":"are potentially huge."},{"time":770991,"text":"Imagine what we could do\nwith 40 percent more funding."},{"time":774294,"text":"We might be able to feed the front row."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779265,"text":"The thing that I fear, the only thing that I fear,"},{"time":781963,"text":"apart from the fact that I've run out of time,"},{"time":783687,"text":"is that the window of opportunity for this idea"},{"time":788404,"text":"is a short one."},{"time":791237,"text":"Today, money creation by central banks"},{"time":795062,"text":"is an accepted policy tool."},{"time":797976,"text":"That may not always be the case."},{"time":800457,"text":"Today there are universally agreed aims"},{"time":804820,"text":"for international aid."},{"time":806711,"text":"That may not always be the case."},{"time":810331,"text":"Today might be the only time"},{"time":812969,"text":"that these two things coincide,"},{"time":815852,"text":"such that we can afford the aid"},{"time":819827,"text":"that we've always aspired to give."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823470,"text":"So, can we print money for international aid?"},{"time":831900,"text":"I seriously believe the question should be,"},{"time":835638,"text":"why not?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":837701,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840514,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}